description:
The 4 Rejects

That morning, his second on Guadalcanal 2nd Lt. Donald Craig found himself in a fire-fight with the enemy! Their mortars pounded and ripped at the perimeter... Lt. Craig's third platoon held fast... only the youthful officer Buckled under the stresses of combat!

Napoleon Innovation (Text Only Story)

The Death Dreamers

These two men were a team... as different as day and night... but in combat, they were practically twins! Sgt. Benny Boondocks, he was called in Baker Company... and Ax Asgood, the company Commander were double trouble in a fire-fight... except on this bitterly cold day... when both men fought with the knowledge that they'd be dead before the sun went down! They knew... because they'd had the dream... and they both believed that it was going to come true...

I'll Die Here

This was Iwo Jima, February, 1945, and half of my platoon had been wiped out on the hill... I was hit in the leg and shoulder! I was happy once the shock had numbed the pain... thinking this battle at least was over for me! But the Japs had different ideas... and they poured out of the ground itself to attack the medics and doctors in the hospital area!

The Marines Landed

In the Philippines, the insurrection from 1899 to 1906 kept Marines fighting bitter Guerilla warfare over terrain they'd return to 40 years later to fight over again! This was bitter jungle warfare against a determined enemy!
